# Commit and push by default

When you finish implementing or fixing something in this repo:

1. **Commit and push** to the tracked remote branch (usually `main`) so Vercel/GitHub stay in sync.
2. **Do not** commit secrets (`.env`, keys), temp files (`.tmp_*`, `supabase/.temp/`), or local-only uploads (e.g. stray `.xlsx`) unless the user explicitly asks.
3. **Skip** commit/push only when the user clearly says not to (e.g. "don't push", "local only", "no commit").

After push, tell the user briefly that deploy will follow via their usual pipeline (e.g. Vercel from GitHub).
